D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fail financially, to become insolvent, to go bankrupt, to become ruined, to run out of the last penny"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of فِلْس (fils)."},"ipa":["/ʔaf.la.sa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34505","headword_ar":"افلس","root":"fls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ifolaAsN","text_ar":"اـِفْلَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufolis","text_ar":"مُفْلِس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which in the common legal acceptation means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bankrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insolvent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had no property remaining:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) as though his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraAhim","text_ar":"دَرَاهِم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or pieces of silver] had become"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluws","text_ar":"فُلُوس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or small copper coins], (S, O, K,) and base money: like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobava","text_ar":"اَخْبَثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ his companions, or friends, became bad, wicked, or deceitful: ” (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became in such a state that it was said he had not a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falos","text_ar":"فَلْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small copper coin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O, K;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqohara","text_ar":"اَقْهَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ he became in a state in which to be overcome, or subdued: ” (S, O:) or as though he became in a state in which to be overcome, or subdued: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became a possessor of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluws","text_ar":"فُلُوس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after he had been a possessor of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraAhim","text_ar":"دَرَاهِم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, Msb:) but properly, [so in the Msb, but I would rather say secondarily, or tropically,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became reduced from a state of ease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"richness, to a state of difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poverty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Afls Alr~ajula","text_ar":"افلس الرَّجُلَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought the man and missed his place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","Msb","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}